      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HULU (2) consistent mare with excellent credentials over this course and distance. Cruised across from the outside gate and showed a ton of grit when third over 1400m at Scone in the Country Cup. Can sit off the good tempo today and put these away. HELLCIBELL (5) fitter after three runs back and looking for this trip now. Beaten for speed and got well out of her ground when chipping away late to run fifth over 1000m at Gunnedah. Can race closer today and finish much closer. KING LARRY (6) talented gelding trained locally. Deep into the prep and will appreciate the 4kg drop in weight after gripping on to run second over 1200m at Quirindi. No shock to see him take this out. RHYTHM IS A DANCER (1) handy fresh gelding who resumes from a lengthy break. Back without a trial and look for him late with the claim. PLAY MY SONG (4) capable on her day and can run into the minor money.",
